  "texts": [
    "However, they often fail to reason logically and augment the information with factual accuracy.",
    "The LLM tends to puzzle feature values together to identify traffic types (e.g., HTTP traffic, DNS queries) effectively, which can be useful for network operators.",
    "However, it struggles to correlate multiple features to identify attack signatures accurately, instead treating individual suspicious features as independent clues of malicious activity.",
    "One significant problem is their tendency to generate nonsensical or unfaithful content, known as \"hallucination\" [18].",
    "These models lack a true comprehension of facts or logical reasoning, relying on learned patterns of word succession within context."
